# Autocomplete Form — Test Suite

A complete test suite for the Autocomplete Form feature, covering manual test scenarios, defect analysis, UI automation (Playwright + TypeScript), and API automation (Jest + Axios).

---

## Project Structure

```
├── README.md
├── docs/
│   ├── 1-requirement-analysis.md      # Ambiguities & assumptions
│   ├── 2-test-scenarios.md            # Top 10 ranked test scenarios
│   ├── 3-defect-identification.md     # FR-05 discrepancies
│   ├── 4-test-cases.md                # Detailed test cases
│   ├── 7-ai-reflection.md             # AI tool usage reflection
│   └── 8-architecture-discussion.md   # Architecture notes
├── tests/
│   ├── ui/
│   │   ├── pages/                     # Page Object Model classes
│   │   ├── tests/                     # Playwright test scripts
│   │   └── config/                    # Playwright config
│   └── api/
│       └── tests/                     # API test scripts (Jest + Axios)
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

---

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js** v18 or higher
- **npm** v9 or higher

---

## Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd autocomplete-form-tests

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Install Playwright browsers
npx playwright install chromium
```

---

## Running Tests

### UI Tests (Playwright)

```bash
# Run all UI tests
npm run test:ui

# Run with browser visible (headed mode)
npm run test:ui:headed

# Run with Playwright HTML report
npm run test:ui:report
```

### API Tests (Jest + Axios)

```bash
# Run all API tests
npm run test:api

# Run with verbose output
npm run test:api:verbose
```

### Run Everything

```bash
npm test
```

